President Barack Obama has proclaimed May 19-25, 2013, as Emergency Medical Services (EMS) Week in the United States. In his proclamation, he acknowledges the dedication and important work of EMS practitioners who provide vital, life-saving services in times of crisis. He specifically mentions the heroic actions of EMS personnel during the Boston Marathon bombings. The President expresses his administration's commitment to supporting these first responders and ensuring they have the necessary resources to aid the American people. He encourages all Americans to show their support for local EMS providers and to take steps to improve personal safety and preparedness.